        "explanation": "As you heard in the Say It Clearly! section of this lesson, questions can have the same word order and form as statements. This type of question often shows surprise, disbelief, or uncertainty, but depending on the intonation used, just about any question can take this form, especially in informal or spoken English. Here are a few examples in context. - *You're tired today?* But you slept for ten hours last night! - *It's Tuesday already?* I thought it was Monday. - *They lost the game?* But they've been winning for weeks! - *Tomorrow is the championship?* I thought it wasn't for a few weeks. ",
