        "topic": "*Go* Plus Gerunds",
        "explanation": "The verb *go* can be followed by certain gerunds in idiomatic expressions used to describe some kind of an activity, usually pleasurable or recreational. *go dancing, go swimming, go sailing, go shopping, go camping* The verb *go* can be in any tense, or with modals. *Let's go dancing.* *We went swimming yesterday, but we should have gone sailing.* *The Parkers have never gone camping before.* ",
